The Bank of England said it provided themoney market with a further 30 mln stg assistance.    This brings the Bank's total help so far today to 120 mlnstg and compares with its upward revised estimate that thesystem would face a shortage of some 1.15 billon stg.    The central bank bought bills for resale to the market inequal amounts on April 1, 2 and 3 at an interest rate of10-7/16 pct. REUTER&#3;